Tests work with browser, interact with ui and emulate user. 

Test project can be opened by Visual Studio 2012 or newest 

Ui test uses next tools:
    1. Webdriver as application driver
    2. Mstests as testrunner

You can run tests on local machine or remote (using Webdriver Grid). 
Tests can be to run against Firefox, Chrome, Internet explorer, Safari (for mac only) 
		
Requirements for Chrome - https://code.google.com/p/selenium/wiki/ChromeDriver
Requirements for Internet explorer - https://code.google.com/p/selenium/wiki/InternetExplorerDriver

How run UI tests on local machine
    1. Get code from github https://github.com/alterm4nn/ChronoZoom
    2. Build project Chronozoom.Entities
    3. Open solution ChronoZoom.Testing.sln
    4. Build the solution  (All requirement packages will be installed)
    5. Setup config (
        a. Set BaseUrl(http://test.chronozoomproject.org) 
        b. BrowserName("chrome", "firefox" or "internet explorer")
    6. Add rules for chromedriver and iedriver in Windows Firewall
    7. Fill UsersInfo.settings - this file is required for AuthorizationTests (The file is added to .gitignore)
    8. Open Visual Studio tests explorer
    9. Run one test
        a. Browser will be started
        b. Homepage will be opened
        c. Test will do something
        d. Browser will be closed
        e. Test will be pass (or may be failed)
